Using Github Page and Hugo to create a blog

learning how to create a personal blog with Githug Page and Hugo theme. 
To reduce the handling the libraries and setting on local computer, all the proceduce will be done online with github editor or creating file on github only.
It will be better to use offline editor as user can preview the final changes.

Step 1:
Login your github account. If you don't have a github account, sign up one.

Step 2
Create a new repository. name the project with this format : username.github.io. 
username refer to your github username.
For example, my username is kacywwww, so i will name my project as kacywwww.github.io
The project name will become the url of the blog. which means my blog url will be https://kacywwww.github.io


